          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 35</h1><p><strong>Questions 31 - 34</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>31 The Pacific is more prone to tsunamis because ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... it has many faults.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... its faults undergo subduction.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... its tectonic plates are bigger than elsewhere.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>32 Underwater landslides cause tsunamis by ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... the creation of underwater holes.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... the movement of sediment and rock underwater.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... the creation of subduction earthquakes.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>33 Tsunamis caused by landslides above sea level and cosmic body impact ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... have a lesser impact than other types of tsunamis.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... are dangerous due to the falling debris they contain.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... can affect coastlines far from the source of impact.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>34 Tsunamis can be difficult to detect because ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... their energy gradually increases as they reach land.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... their speed builds up below the water.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... of the low height of the waves.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
